
!!!Skolt Saami adjectives

!!Intro

The lexicon ''AdjectiveRoot'' is where we list the adjectives. However, this file still contains only a handful of words because almost nothing is done for adjectives yet.

!!Categories

Adjectives in Skolt Saami inflect for attributive and predicative state. Predicative adjectives inflect for number. Attributive adjectives inflect for number and case only if they are used as substantives. Beside inflection, adjective morphology in Skolt Saami exhibits derivational forms for comparation.  

Hence the following morphological features and feature values are relevant:
*STATE
** +Pred (predicative)
** +Attr (attributive)

*COMPARATION
** +Comp (comparative)
** +Superl (superlative)

*NUMBER
** +Sg
** +Pl

*CASE
** +Nom
** +Gen
** +Acc
** +Ill
** +Ine
** +Ela
** +Com
** +Ess
** +Par
** +Abe

According to different stem vowels and choice for different predicative and/or attributive suffix allomorphs, adjectives can be devided into the following classes.

!!A1
+Pred always monosyllabic, strong grade, (non)palatalized (= noun class 1)
+Attr always weak grade, (non)palatalized, suffix -(V)s (= noun class ??)
+Comp always weak grade, (non)palatalized, suffix -ab
+Superl always weak grade, (non)palatalized, suffix -mõs

AdjClass A1 has three sub-classes, which are defined by the vowels -a- vs. -â- vs. -e- in the attributive suffixes

AdjClass A1a
* luäǯ'ǯ-Ø luäǯǯ-as luäǯǯ-ab luäǯǯ-mõs

AdjClass A1â
* jõll jõõllâs jõõllab jõõllmõs

AdjClass A1e (pred-attr-comp-superl)
* cueˊǩǩ-Ø cueˊjj-es cueˊjj-ab cueˊjj-mõs
* čeäˊp'p-Ø čieˊpp-es čieˊpp-ab čieˊpp-mõs


!!A4
+Pred always bisyllabic, weak grade, (non)palatalized, suffix -(V)s (= noun class 4)
+Attr always monosyllabic strong grade, (non)palatalized (= noun class 1)
+Comp always strong grade, nonpalatalized, suffix -sab
+Superl always strong grade, nonpalatalized, suffix -sumus

AdjClass A4 has two sub-classes, which are defined by the vowels -a- vs. -â- vs. -e- in the predicative suffixes

